Saahitya 2016 is IITM's first ever Litfest and we're organising a fun
contest for the same!

We want you to get creative with song lyrics for this one!

*Sir Mix-a-lot!*

Making parodies of songs is serious business and one that we take
seriously! In fact, there is a bounty of *INR 6000/- *for those fair
maidens and fine sires who send us that perfect parody.

So, get out your quills, plug in your headphones and send us your entries!

The rules are

   1. Entries should not be longer than 2 pages.
   2. Entries should be in English.
   3. Theme for the parodies could be any popular book, movie or TV show.
   4. Entries should be parodies of an English song, preferably a popular
   one.
   5. Excessive profanity is discouraged.
   6. A PDF entry can be sent however you get *extra points for sending a
   video of yourself singing the parody!*
   7. Prizes for 1st, 2nd, 3rd are 3k, 2k, 1k respectively.

The deadline for the contest* 2nd April, 11.59 PM. *
Please send in your entries to* iitmmusicclub@gmail.com
<iitmmusicclub@gmail.com>* before the deadline and mention the following

   - Name of the original song and your inspiration for the parody
   - Your Name and your College
   - Your Phone number


